def numPoints(darts, r):
    n = len(darts)
    result = 1

    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(n):
            cnt = 0
            for k in range(n):
                dx = darts[i][0] - darts[k][0]
                dy = darts[i][1] - darts[k][1]
                if (dx * dx + dy * dy) ** 0.5 <= r:
                    cnt += 1

            if cnt > result:
                result = cnt

    return result
```

    The algorithm is fairly straightforward. We iterate through all pairs of darts and try to place the dartboard center on each pair. Then, for each pair of darts, we check how many darts are within the distance `r` from both darts in the pair. The answer is the maximum count of darts that can be covered by the dartboard for all pairs of darts.

The time complexity of the algorithm is O(n^3), where n is the number of darts. In the worst case, there can be up to 100 darts, so the algorithm will be fast enough.

